WENN MOUNT ETNA: Europe's highest volcano has begun to erup 
Mount Etna has erupted in a fiery show of lava in eastern Sicily – sending giant orange fountains of lava spewing into the air. 
The firework show can be seen from ehe city of Catania and the resort town of Taormina. 
WENN ERUPTION: Mount Etna is spewing lava 
GOOGLE 
Etna is Europe's highest and most active volcano. 
The fire-spitting mountain began to spurt lava last night. STUNNING images of a volcano erupting at night Thursday, 9th February 2017 Photographer Denis Budkov captured these stunning images of the Klyuchevskaya Sopka volcano in Russia. The photographer used long exposures to capture the night sky and the volcano during a series of four eruptions. 1 / 12 Caters News Agency Volcano erupting at night. 
Volcanologists are classing the eruption as 'Strombolian' - a category characterized by explosive bursts of activity during which cinder, ash and smoke are ejected from the crater with great force. 
Daily Star Online previously revealed fears of a supervolcano "worse than Vesuvius" with Campi Flegrei lurking underneath Naples in Italy. Explosive Volcano Eruptions Wednesday, 27th July 2016 These are the explosive images of some of the worlds most astonishing volcanic eruptions. Spectacular snaps capture lava spewing down the side of Kilauea, ash spitting from craters and plumes of smoke rising thousands of feet in the air. 1 / 22 The Asahi Shimbun via Getty Imag Stunning photos as a dirty thunderstorm occurs over Mount Sakurajima as the volcano erupts violently in Japan 
Italy's National Institute of Geophysics and Vulcanology said the eruptions don't currently present a danger to people or property. 
in 1669, a massive eruption from Mount Etna is recorded to have killed more than 20,000 people.
